			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "The housefly , Musca domestica ( Linnaeus , 1758 ) ( Diptera : Muscidae ) , has been implicated as a mechanical vector of numerous pathogens .",
			"relation": "elaboration"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In this study 2000 aerial net - captured houseflies were examined for their ability to harbour Newcastle disease virus ( NDV ) .",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "In an adjacent study , laboratory - reared flies were experimentally exposed to NDV La Sota strain .",
			"relation": "elaboration"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "The virus was detected in the dissected gastrointestinal tract of laboratory - exposed flies for up to 72 h post - exposure ,",
